"{\n    \"Title\": \"Thunder Bay Port AuthorityNotes to Financial Statements\",\n    \"row 1\": \"December 31, 2019 (expressed in CAD $)\",\n    \"row 2\": \"5. Long Term Investments\",\n    \"row 3\": \"(a) Recognition and initial measurement\",\n    \"row 4\": \"The Port Authority recognizes debt instruments on the date on which they are originated. The\",\n    \"row 5\": \"instruments are initially measured at fair value.\",\n    \"row 6\": \"(b) Classification and subsequent measurement\",\n    \"row 7\": \"The Port Authority classifies its bonds at amortized cost as the documented investment strategy\",\n    \"row 8\": \"requires the instruments to be held to collect contractual cash flows to maturity.\",\n    \"row 9\": \"(c) Derecognition\",\n    \"row 10\": \"The Port Authority derecognizes investments when the contractual rights to the cash flows from\",\n    \"row 11\": \"the investment expires. On derecognition, if not held to maturity, the difference between the\",\n    \"row 12\": \"carrying amount at the date of derecognition and the consideration received is recognized in profit\",\n    \"row 13\": \"or loss.\",\n    \"row 14\": \"(d) Amortised cost measurement\",\n    \"row 15\": \"The following is a breakdown of the investments:\",\n    \"row 16\": \"2019 2018\",\n    \"row 17\": \"Cost Fair Value Cost Fair Value\",\n    \"row 18\": \"Cash balances in investments S$ 906,787 $ 906,787 $ 2,427,769 $ 2,427,769\",\n    \"row 19\": \"Accrued interest 117,479 117,479 114,447 114,447\",\n    \"row 20\": \"Bonds and debentures\",\n    \"row 21\": \"-maturing within one year 5,496,152 5,442,858 4,514,010 4,391,098\",\n    \"row 22\": \"-maturing between 1 and 5 years 7,763,901 7,951,445 8,831,978 8,925,968\",\n    \"row 23\": \"-maturing in more than 5 years 2,109,173 2,164,445 2,450,202 2,410,289\",\n    \"row 24\": \"$ 16,393,492 $16,583,014 $ 18,338,406 $ 18,269,571\",\n    \"row 25\": \"The bonds and debentures, which are held in provincial and federal crown and corporate issues,\",\n    \"row 26\": \"have effective yields ranging from approximately 2.15% to 5.12% (2018 - 2.10% to 5.12%).\"\n}"